<task id="044" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>UI tests — EmailComposer `mode=forward` (attachments carried + deselect) + `mode=draft` (resume + Save Draft + Send transitions)</title>
    <phase>Wave 2 — EmailComposer Code Page + Entry Surfaces</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>036</dependencies>
    <blocks>099</blocks>
    <tags>ui-test, e2e-test, frontend</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Two related UI tests in one task; deterministic scenarios; testing FR-12 + FR-13 modes</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>I</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Parallel-safe with 041, 042, 043, 045 — independent record-level mutations per test</parallel-reason>
    <fr-refs>FR-12, FR-13, FR-18</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Execute end-to-end UI tests for TWO modes:
    1. **Forward mode** (`mode=forward&id={existing-record-guid}`) per FR-12: carries attachments by default with deselect capability; `subject` prefixed `Fwd:`; `sprk_inreplyto` stamped on new record
    2. **Draft mode** (`mode=draft&id={existing-draft-guid}`) per FR-13: loads saved draft values; Save Draft persists; Send transitions `statuscode` to Sent and triggers Graph SendMail

    Use the `ui-test` skill. Verify zero console errors per test. Verify dark mode smoke per ADR-021.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke UI test engineer. Familiar with FR-12 (forward semantics), FR-13 (draft semantics), `statuscode` lifecycle on `sprk_communication`, and attachment carry/deselect logic.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Two UI test passes (forward + draft) documented in `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/044-ui-test-forward-draft.md` with pass/fail per assertion, console-error inventory, Dataverse-side stamp/statuscode verification, and dark mode smoke observations.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-12: forward pre-fills new compose; to/cc blank; subject = `Fwd: ${original.subject}`; body wraps original; attachments carried by default (user can deselect); associations carried; `sprk_inreplyto` stamped.

      Per FR-13: draft mode loads from `sprk_communication` where `statuscode = Draft`. Both Send and Save Draft actions functional. Save Draft updates same record; Send transitions `statuscode` to `Sent` and triggers Graph SendMail.

      Test data: requires (a) an existing sent record with attachments for forward test, (b) an existing draft record for draft test. Create them via task 041 (compose) if not present.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/044-ui-test-forward-draft.md (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-12">Forward carries attachments by default; deselect removes from send; `sprk_inreplyto` stamped</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-13">Draft loads saved values; Save Draft persists; Send transitions statuscode</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Dark mode compliance smoke per test</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Use `{org}`, `{existing-record-guid}`, `{existing-draft-guid}` placeholders</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Dev environment only</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No `.claude/` writes in this Wave 2 task</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/ui-test/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="UI test for mode with side effects" location=".claude/skills/ui-test/SKILL.md">
        Post-Send: query Dataverse to verify field stamps and statuscode transitions.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Forward mode — attachments carried + deselect + sprk_inreplyto stamp">
      <navigation>
        <url>https://{org}/WebResources/sprk_emailcomposer?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22forward%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-record-guid}%22%7D</url>
        <description>Forward mode on an existing record that HAS at least 2 attachments</description>
      </navigation>
      <steps>
        <step order="1">Navigate to URL; wait for app mount + record load</step>
        <step order="2">Verify zero console errors on cold load</step>
        <step order="3">Verify To field is empty (forward does NOT auto-fill to original sender)</step>
        <step order="4">Verify Cc field is empty</step>
        <step order="5">Verify Subject field prefilled with `Fwd: ${original.subject}` (no double-prefix if already `Fwd:`)</step>
        <step order="6">Verify Body field prefilled with empty user area + divider + quoted original body</step>
        <step order="7">Verify Attachments list shows BOTH original attachments with checkbox/selected state (carried by default)</step>
        <step order="8">Verify Associations carried from original</step>
        <step order="9">Deselect ONE attachment (uncheck its select control)</step>
        <step order="10">Fill To: `forward-test@example.com`</step>
        <step order="11">Click Send; wait for response</step>
        <step order="12">Verify success state</step>
        <step order="13">Verify Dataverse-side: new record has `sprk_inreplyto` pointing to original; attached driveItem IDs = 1 (the deselected one was removed)</step>
        <step order="14">Verify zero console errors throughout</step>
      </steps>
      <expected-outcomes>
        <outcome>Forward mode prefills Subject (Fwd:) + Body (wrapped); To/Cc empty</outcome>
        <outcome>Attachments carried by default with deselect capability</outcome>
        <outcome>Deselected attachments NOT included in send</outcome>
        <outcome>New record has `sprk_inreplyto` stamp</outcome>
        <outcome>Zero console errors</outcome>
      </expected-outcomes>
      <dark-mode-check>
        <step>Toggle dark mode; verify forward UI adapts including attachment list</step>
      </dark-mode-check>
      <console-error-check>
        <target>0 errors</target>
      </console-error-check>
    </test>

    <test name="Draft mode — load saved values + Save Draft + Send transitions statuscode">
      <navigation>
        <url>https://{org}/WebResources/sprk_emailcomposer?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22draft%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-draft-guid}%22%7D</url>
        <description>Draft mode on an existing `sprk_communication` record with `statuscode = Draft`</description>
      </navigation>
      <steps>
        <step order="1">Navigate to URL; wait for app mount + record load</step>
        <step order="2">Verify zero console errors on cold load</step>
        <step order="3">Verify To field loaded with previously-saved values</step>
        <step order="4">Verify Subject field loaded with previously-saved value</step>
        <step order="5">Verify Body field loaded with previously-saved content</step>
        <step order="6">Verify both `Save Draft` AND `Send` action buttons are present</step>
        <step order="7">Modify Subject to add ` [updated]` suffix</step>
        <step order="8">Click `Save Draft`; wait for response</step>
        <step order="9">Verify success state for Save Draft</step>
        <step order="10">Verify Dataverse-side: same record's Subject has the ` [updated]` suffix; `statuscode` STILL = Draft</step>
        <step order="11">Now click `Send`; wait for response</step>
        <step order="12">Verify success state for Send</step>
        <step order="13">Verify Dataverse-side: same record's `statuscode` = Sent (transitioned); `sprk_internetmessageid` populated post-send (per task 003)</step>
        <step order="14">Verify zero console errors throughout</step>
      </steps>
      <expected-outcomes>
        <outcome>Draft mode loads saved values</outcome>
        <outcome>Save Draft updates same record; statuscode stays Draft</outcome>
        <outcome>Send transitions statuscode to Sent</outcome>
        <outcome>`sprk_internetmessageid` populated post-send (best-effort)</outcome>
        <outcome>Zero console errors</outcome>
      </expected-outcomes>
      <dark-mode-check>
        <step>Toggle dark mode; verify draft UI + dual action buttons adapt</step>
      </dark-mode-check>
      <console-error-check>
        <target>0 errors</target>
      </console-error-check>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify task 036 (Code Page deploy) successful.</step>
    <step order="2">Identify test data:
      - Forward test: existing `sprk_communication` record with 2+ attachments (create via task 041 if missing)
      - Draft test: existing `sprk_communication` record with `statuscode = Draft` (create via task 041 by clicking Save Draft if missing)
    </step>
    <step order="3">Invoke `ui-test` skill — Chrome session, logged in.</step>
    <step order="4">Execute forward-mode test scenario; capture results.</step>
    <step order="5">Execute draft-mode test scenario; capture results.</step>
    <step order="6">Post-Send: query Dataverse to verify field stamps + statuscode transitions for each test.</step>
    <step order="7">Toggle dark mode; smoke-verify both forward + draft UIs.</step>
    <step order="8">Document results in `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/044-ui-test-forward-draft.md` with two test sections.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 044 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="ui-test">Skill — Chrome browser automation</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-mcp-usage">Verify Dataverse-side field stamps + statuscode transitions</tool>
    <tool name="write">Test results note</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/044-ui-test-forward-draft.md (NEW — two test sections)</output>
    <output type="test-result">Forward mode test + Draft mode test pass/fail logged</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Forward mode prefills Subject (Fwd:) + Body; carries attachments; deselect removes from send.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Forward Send stamps `sprk_inreplyto` on new record.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Draft mode loads saved values; both Save Draft and Send actions present.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Save Draft updates same record; statuscode stays Draft.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Send transitions statuscode to Sent; `sprk_internetmessageid` populated.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero console errors in both tests.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Dark mode smoke checks pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Test results documented for both modes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No `.claude/` files modified in this task.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Parallel-group I: safe to run alongside 041, 042, 043, 045.

    Test data setup may require running task 041 (compose) FIRST to create the forward source record (with attachments) and the draft source record (with `statuscode = Draft`). If running in true parallel, ensure either (a) test data is pre-provisioned, or (b) this task's pre-step creates the records.

    `statuscode` values: in Dataverse, `sprk_communication.statuscode` has typed values. Per R2 spec, Draft = 1 (Active state), Sent = a different value. Use `Xrm.WebApi` or skill helper to verify the transition.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>
      Load all `<knowledge><files>` before starting. Apply STANDARD rigor per `<rigor-hint>`. Invoke `ui-test` skill for browser automation. Two separate test scenarios — document each independently.
    </protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
